## What reaches Typesense

Read-only collection inspection:

```sh
KEY=$(secrets lease typesense_api_key)
curl -fsS http://localhost:8108/collections/{runs_dev,run_chunks_dev} \
  -H "X-TYPESENSE-API-KEY: $KEY" | jq '{name,num_documents,fields}'
```

```text
runs_dev: 40,949 documents
  runtimes: pi 40,000; claude-code 820; codex 129
  machines: blaine 18,967; flagg 10,904; dark-wizard 9,876; panda 1,202
run_chunks_dev: 272,829 documents
  runtimes: pi 236,451; claude-code 30,989; codex 5,389
  machines: blaine 194,417; flagg 60,014; dark-wizard 14,843; panda 3,555
```

`dark-wizard` is a legacy/alias machine identity and was not merged into flagg
for this matrix. That identity split must be handled explicitly during observer
deduplication.

`runs_dev` fields: identity/access (`user_id`, `machine_id`, `agent_runtime`,
`readable_by`), lineage (`parent_run_id`, `root_run_id`, `conversation_id`),
model/tags, timing, turn/tool counts, `token_total`, touched files/skills/entities,
status, full text, and raw JSONL path/bytes/SHA-256. `run_chunks_dev` holds
`run_id`, chunk index/role/text, embedding/model, token count, timing/access,
lineage/tags, runtime, and machine. Raw run blobs under
`~/.joelclaw/runs-dev/...` are authoritative; both Typesense collections are
rebuildable derived indexes (`docs/runbooks/typesense-session-indexing.md`).

Seven-day Typesense volume, counting unique `conversation_id` rather than
capture-delta runs:

| Machine | Pi | Claude | Codex |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| flagg | 207 sessions / 5.82M tokens | 20 / 1.20M | 0 / 0 |
| blaine | 69 / 1.10M | 8 / 84K | 0 / 0 |
| panda | 0 / 0 | 0 / 0 | 0 / 0 |

Command receipt:

```sh
curl -fsS -G http://localhost:8108/collections/runs_dev/documents/export \
  -H "X-TYPESENSE-API-KEY: $KEY" \
  --data-urlencode 'filter_by=machine_id:=<m> && agent_runtime:=<r> && started_at:>=1783288068369' \
  --data-urlencode 'include_fields=id,conversation_id,root_run_id,token_total' \
| jq -s '{runs:length,unique_conversations:...,tokens:...}'
```

## Change ledger status

Pi runtime v1 runs **only on flagg** today.

```sh
ls -l ~/.pi/agent/extensions/change-ledger
wc -l ~/.local/state/joelclaw/change-ledger/2026-07-12.jsonl
ssh joel@blaine 'test -L ~/.pi/agent/extensions/change-ledger || echo MISSING; test -d ~/.local/state/joelclaw/change-ledger || echo MISSING'
```

```text
flagg symlink -> /Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/pi-tools/change-ledger
flagg ledger: 509 records at inspection time
blaine ledger symlink=MISSING; ledger dir=MISSING
panda: no change-ledger extension observed
```

Coverage is successful Pi `write`/`edit` tool results with pre/post blob hashes,
per-turn `changeSetId`, repo/worktree/HEAD identity, plus deterministic
commit-attribution by blob equality. Bash mutations get an unattributed marker.
Claude, Codex, bash worktree diffing, supersession, and rewrite lineage are not
covered. Source: `.brain/projects/brain-graph/instrument-session-change-ledger.svx`.

## Named gaps

1. **Codex indexing is broken on active machines.** Flagg has 68 and blaine has
   3 raw Codex transcripts in the seven-day window, but Typesense has zero new
   Codex runs. Blaine’s hook says `missing session_id/transcript_path`.
2. **Panda Claude is raw-only.** A 17.3 MB Claude transcript was active on
   2026-07-12 while Panda’s newest Claude index record is 2026-06-23.
3. **The change ledger is flagg-only and Pi-only.** Blaine, Panda, Claude, and
   Codex cannot yet supply deterministic session→commit provenance.
4. **Machine identity is split.** Typesense contains both `flagg` and legacy
   `dark-wizard`; observer cursors cannot treat those as separate physical
   machines without double-counting history.
5. **Outbox backlogs remain large and stale:** blaine has 6,863 JSON payloads
   (newest 2026-06-22); panda has 4,268 (newest 2026-06-21). These do not explain
   fresh Codex loss by themselves, but they are evidence that delivery repair
   has previously accumulated debt.

## What this means for observer design

Do not trigger observers directly from raw file counts or assume all nine cells
are equivalent. Use accepted/indexed run deltas with a per-runtime,
per-machine cursor, normalize `dark-wizard` to the verified flagg identity, and
emit an explicit capture-health event when raw freshness outruns index freshness.

Budget for the healthy indexed stream first: roughly **43 unique captured
conversations/day** across flagg and blaine (Pi + Claude), not the 800-ish raw
JSONL files/week and not the thousands of per-turn capture runs. Preserve raw
paths/SHA provenance so Codex and Panda can be backfilled after their capture
edges are repaired. Treat change-ledger provenance as optional enrichment until
coverage expands beyond flagg Pi; never fabricate commit attribution for the
other eight cells.
